Merge pull request #15 from indygreg/readme

Self advertise content location

advertise how to change content

I don't think people realize it is possible to define new content to put
on the screens in the offices. To spread this knowledge, we introduce a
new piece of content that tells people where the content lives.

The image is currently the infamous "johnath pointing" image with "Your
Content Here" (in Comic Sans of course) with a URL to the moz-corsica
GitHub project. And just to troll our UX people, the image features two
colors from Mozilla's brand guidelines that shouldn't be used in direct
contrast. This will surely invite others to add "proper" content.

better usage docs

I figured out how to set up a local server, so I documented it.

Merge pull request #12 from lsblakk/patch-3

Connection details for remoties
Adjusted details to address questions about location

Connection details for remoties

I put this up in Yammer and people are confused by the current instructions on how to get this up and running by themselves.  I hope this might help non webdev folks have an instance up in their home offices.  Took out the stuff about changing the location tag since that seems to be hit or miss on my end, it's very opaque and the average new user will not need it for now.  I'm happy to try and write more documentation for it to flesh out the intended usage.
